There is so much bad treatment of our teachers and students that it should be in a worse state to say the least…of course the Ministry looks out for those they are directly employed by. There have been many many attempts to start free tutoring/scout like programs and a few of them working to some degree. The Government likes freedom but also wants to control your life at the same time. This is not a good way to achieve freedom and justice. Thanks Faisal for this wonderful blog and the content was a great read. 🙂

I notice that you used the word transformation rather than revolution. The revolutionary transformation of the society will also require modernising the culture such as bring about a tall paradigm shift. I think that the urge to flee is a manifestation of this. “we have an feudal philosopher-king-mistress and the swamp beasts of jealosy and corruption are being offered a 31 cent tax that the rest of the global community has long upgraded to a beer”. This beautiful imagery of Sr F/Absalom Martin is predominant in the south two of the 31 states and it leads to the proliferation of private universities. The management consultants who should be able to lead the transformation don’t have the experience of running schools itself never mind the examination process.
